				\begin{document}$${\rm{ \% }}neurotoxicity=100\times \frac{Testwell-Median\,Low\,Controls}{Median\,High\,Controls-Median\,Low\,Controls}$$\end{document}%neurotoxicity=100×Testwell−MedianLowControlsMedianHighControls−MedianLowControlswhere Testwell refers to compound wells and High and Low Control wells represent wells treated with 10 μM Brefeldin-A and DMSO, respectively. Modeling the normalized data on a standard distribution for all test wells we found a response of 40% to 100% to occur for those samples that were one standard deviation above the mean. These compounds were designated as hits.
